{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782034162,"nonce":"aGz7fGHZ9Y9i+PbuFGVAYngwI+0=","title":"Table derive: no bytea/Vec\u003cu8\u003e column binding","message":"The `#[derive(Table)]` machinery has no column binding for `Vec\u003cu8\u003e` (bytea), even though the SQL type exists: `SqlType::Bytes` =\u003e \"bytea\" is wired in sql.rs (render) and introspect.rs.\n\nA table field typed `pub data: C::Type\u003c'scope, Vec\u003cu8\u003e\u003e` fails to compile when used in queries:\n\n  error[E0277]: the trait `squealy::ColumnNullability` is not implemented for `Vec\u003cu8\u003e`\n      --\u003e .../src/column.rs:10\n  error[E0277]: the trait `squealy::ExprKind` is not implemented for `Vec\u003cu8\u003e`\n      = note: required for `Vec\u003cu8\u003e` to implement `squealy::IntoAssignmentValue\u003c...\u003e`\n  error[E0599]: the method `where_`/`insert` exists ... but its trait bounds were not satisfied\n      doesn't satisfy `Vec\u003cu8\u003e: squealy::ColumnNullability`\n\nRepro: derive Table with a `C::Type\u003c'scope, Vec\u003cu8\u003e\u003e` column, then call .insert()/.where_()/.select() on it.\n\nFix: add the column-binding impls for `Vec\u003cu8\u003e` (and likely `Option\u003cVec\u003cu8\u003e\u003e`) alongside the existing primitive impls (where String/i64/Uuid get ColumnNullability + ExprKind + IntoAssignmentValue + the from-row decode), mapping to SqlType::Bytes. The SQL/DDL side already renders bytea; only the Rust binding is missing.\n\nContext: blocks gitana-2 storing sealed CI secrets (ciphertext/wrapped_dek) as bytea; worked around downstream with hex String columns for now.","files":null}]}